Running tests requires GoogleTest (https://github.com/google/googletest) and
CMSSW software
0.  Set CMSSW in release area
    $> cmsenv
1. Install googletest library to TopBrussels root folder
    $> cd ${TOPBRUSSELS_ROOT}
    $> wget https://github.com/google/googletest/archive/release-1.7.0.zip
    $> unzip  wget https://github.com/google/googletest/archive/release-1.7.0.zip
    $> cd googletest-release-1.7.0
    $> mkdir build; cd build
    $> cmake ..
    $> make
    $> cd ..
    $> mkdir lib
    $> cp build/lib*.a lib

2. Build tests
    $> cd ${TOPTREEANALYSISBASE_ROOT}
    $> mkdir build; cd build
    $> cmake .. -DCMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=Release -DTOPBRUSSELS_INCLUDE_DIRS=${TOPBRUSSELS_ROOT} \
        -DGTEST_ROOT=${TOPBRUSSELS_ROOT}/googletest-release-1.7.0 \
        -DROOT_DIR=$ROOTSYS/cmake
    $> make
3. Test
    $> ctest

